
JAN. 21, 2018

Abigail Wadsworth Darby and Clayton Andrew Robinson were married Jan. 20 at St. Thomas Church Fifth Avenue in New York. The Rev. Michael D. Spurlock, an Episcopal priest, led the ceremony.
Mrs. Robinson, 31, is a vice president in cross-asset sales group focusing on hedge fund clients within the securities division of Goldman Sachs in New York. She graduated cum laude from Harvard.
She is the daughter of Mary Wadsworth Darby and Lawrence A. Darby III of Tuxedo Park, N.Y. The bride’s father is a lawyer in Tuxedo Park. Her mother is the chief representative of Cheung Kong Graduate School of Business (Americas) in New York. She is also a director of Industrial and Commercial Bank of China (USA) and is the chairwoman of the Hong Kong Association of New York.
Mr. Robinson, 30, is a vice president in the financial institutions investment banking group at JPMorgan Chase in New York. He graduated from the University of Pennsylvania.
He is a son of Debra Loria Robinson and Troy M. Robinson of Quitman, Tex. The groom’s mother is the chief executive of Wood County Electric Cooperative in Quitman, an electric power distributor in East Texas. His father is the vice chairman of BTH Bank in Quitman.
The couple met in 2012 through friends in New York.
